{"questionId":"28284","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ammonium nitrate, NH<sub>4</sub>NO<sub>3</sub>, is used as a high nitrogen fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Cold packs contain ammonium nitrate and water separated by a membrane.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the standard entropy change, Δ<em>S</em><sup>⦵</sup>, for the dissolution of&nbsp;ammonium nitrate.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">S<sup>⦵</sup>NH<sub>4</sub>NO<sub>3</sub> (s) = 151.1 J mol<sup>−1</sup> K<sup>−1</sup></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">S<sup>⦵</sup>NH<sub>4</sub>NO<sub>3 </sub>(aq) = 259.8 J mol<sup>−1</sup> K<sup>−1</sup></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Δ</mtext><mi>S</mi><mo>°</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>259</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi>J</mi><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi><mi>o</mi><msup><mi>l</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>151</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>J</mi><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi><mi>o</mi><msup><mi>l</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math>» 108.7 «J mol<sup>−1</sup> K<sup>−1</sup>» ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"28284","referenceCode":"22N.2.hl.TZ0.1d.v","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the standard entropy change, ΔS⦵, for the dissolution of ammonium nitrate. S⦵NH4NO3 (s) = 151.1 J mol−1 K−1 S⦵NH4NO3 (aq) = 259.8 J mol−1 K−1","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.v","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry","15.2 Entropy and spontaneity","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 15: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}